[SN]TITLE[SN]
Freedivers to hold their breath for colleague who died

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Friends of the freediving champion Natalia Molchanova, who died last month, are appealing to members of the diving community to hold their breath for a minute to remember her.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Molchanova was the most successful woman in the history of the sport, with 41 records across several disciplines.
She was undertaking a routine dive off the coast of Ibiza in August when she failed to resurface.
The minute's breath hold will take place at 18:30 GMT on Friday.
Aida International, the sport's governing body, has asked people taking part to send photographs, messages or videos for a compilation to be shown at the World Championships.
Freediving is diving without using breathing apparatus.
