Tributes poured in from the freediving community when Molchanova went missing. The 53-year-old Russian is presumed dead, though her body has not been found.
New Zealand freediving champion William Trubridge called her the "queen of freediving" and said the sport had lost its greatest competitor.
Only one person has lost their life in a competitive freediving event. About five people are thought to have died while training.
